1. Theoretical models                                             7034 1451
 The POD code is based on the spherical optical model, the        7034 1451
distorted-wave Born approximaiton (DWBA), one-component exciton   7034 1451
preequilibrium model, and the Hauser-Feshbach-Moldauer statis-    7034 1451
tical model.  With the preequilibrium model, semi-empirical       7034 1451
pickup and knockout process can be taken into account for         7034 1451
composite-particle emission.  The gamma-ray emission from the     7034 1451
compound nucleus can be calculated within the framework of the    7034 1451
exciton model.  The code is capable of reading in particle        7034 1451
transmission coefficients calculated by separate spherical or     7034 1451
coupled-channel optical model code. In this evaluation, the OPTMAN7034 1451
/4/ code was employed for neutrons, while the ECIS code           7034 1451
/6/ was adopted for charged particles.                            7034 1451
